Name: female breast cancer
Definition: A breast cancer that develops from breast tissue in females.

Name: estrogen-receptor positive breast cancer
Definition: A breast cancer that is characterized by the presence of estrogen receptors.

Name: estrogen-receptor negative breast cancer
Definition: A breast cancer that is characterized by the absence of estrogen receptors.

Name: progesterone-receptor positive breast cancer
Definition: A breast cancer that is characterized by the presence of progesterone receptors.

Name: progesterone-receptor negative breast cancer
Definition: A breast cancer that is characterized by the absence of progesterone receptors.

Name: Her2-receptor positive breast cancer
Definition: A breast cancer that is characterized by the presence of Her2 receptors.

Name: Her2-receptor negative breast cancer
Definition: A breast cancer that is characterized by the absence of Her2 receptors.

Name: triple-receptor negative breast cancer
Definition: A breast cancer that is characterized by the absence of estrogen

Name: male breast cancer
Definition: A breast cancer that occurs in males.

Name: breast myoepithelial neoplasm
Definition: A breast cancer that arises from myoepithelial cells

Name: breast granular cell tumor
Definition: A breast cancer that is believed to arises_from Schwann cells.

Name: breast malignant phyllodes tumor
Definition: A breast cancer that is characterized by a prominent infiltrative border

Name: breast sarcoma
Definition: A breast cancer that has_material_basis_in abnormally proliferating cells derives_from mesenchymal cells.

Name: obsolete postpartum acute renal failure
Definition: A breast cancer that has_material_basis_in abnormally proliferating cells derives_from mesenchymal cells.

Name: breast carcinoma
Definition: A breast cancer that has_material_basis_in abnormally proliferating cells derives_from epithelial cells.

Name: obsolete breast hamartoma
Definition: A breast cancer that has_material_basis_in abnormally proliferating cells derives_from epithelial cells.

Name: obsolete hamartoma
Definition: A breast cancer that has_material_basis_in abnormally proliferating cells derives_from epithelial cells.

Name: malignant breast melanoma
Definition: A breast cancer that arises_from melanocytes.

Name: breast lymphoma
Definition: A breast cancer that arises_from lymphocytes.

Name: breast malignant eccrine spiradenoma
Definition: A breast cancer that arises_from cutaneous sweat glands and is characterized by a focus of benign spiradenoma within or adjacent to the malignant tumor
Synonym: malignant Eccrine Spiradenoma of the breast
